inen die fruchtbaren Wechselwirkungen zwischen Tillich und seinem akademischen Umfeld im Blick auf die Genese einer genuin 'kritischen Theologie' deutlich; zugleich entsteht ein konturschärferes Bild der geistigen Situation der Frankfurter Universität unmittelbar vor der nationalsozialistischen Machtübernahme.   aThis volume examines the multifaceted origins of Paul Tillich’s “critical theology” during the Frankfurt years (1929–1933) from the perspectives of source and reception history. In this way, it provides a compelling picture of the rich interactions between Tillich and his academic environment as well as the spiritual situation at the University of Frankfurt just before the National Socialist takeover.   aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 23. Jun 2020) 4aFrankfurt am Main. 4aKulturtheologie. 4aPhilosophy of Religion. 4aReligionsphilosophie. 4aTheology of Culture. 4aTillich, Paul. 7aRELIGION / Christian Theology / History.2bisacsh1 aSchreiber, Gerhard , eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aSchulz, Heiko, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2015z978311070098508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2015z9783110439687oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Theology, Relig. Studies, Jewish Studies 2015z9783110438727oZDB-23-DGF0 cEPUBz97831104337530 cprintz978311044126040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311043416340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110434163423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9783110434163.jpg  a978-3-11-070098-5  DG Plus eBook-Package 2015b2015  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGFb2015